items.title: Awesome Ember
items.content_text:
### Packages / Modifiers

*   [ember-on-modifier (⭐37)](https://github.com/buschtoens/ember-on-modifier) - An implementation of the `{{on}}` element modifier shown in the Modifiers RFC #353.
*   [ember-render-modifiers (⭐87)](https://github.com/emberjs/ember-render-modifiers) - Implements did-insert / did-update / will-destroy modifiers for RFC #415.

### Packages / Articles

*   [Ember.js ❤Angle Brackets. A Migration Guide & Cheat Sheet](https://medium.com/@AveryBloom/ff309d6effdf)
*   [Coming Soon in Ember Octane - Part 1: Native Classes](https://www.pzuraq.com/coming-soon-in-ember-octane-part-1-native-classes/)
*   [Coming Soon in Ember Octane - Part 2: Angle Brackets Syntax & Named Arguments](https://www.pzuraq.com/coming-soon-in-ember-octane-part-2-angle-brackets-and-named-arguments/)
*   [Nested components and angle brackets, a sneaky solution](https://locks.svbtle.com/nested-components-and-angle-brackets)
items.content_html:
Packages / Modifiers

  • ember-on-modifier (⭐37) - An implementation of the {{on}} element modifier shown in the Modifiers RFC #353.
  • ember-render-modifiers (⭐87) - Implements did-insert / did-update / will-destroy modifiers for RFC #415.

Packages / Articles

  • Ember.js ❤Angle Brackets. A Migration Guide & Cheat Sheet
  • Coming Soon in Ember Octane - Part 1: Native Classes
  • Coming Soon in Ember Octane - Part 2: Angle Brackets Syntax & Named Arguments
  • Nested components and angle brackets, a sneaky solution
